The paper deals with proof complexity, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that studies the resources required to prove mathematical statements. Specifically, the paper focuses on the space complexity of resolution proofs, which is a topic that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also makes use of techniques from graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
